<paragraph id="8BB736C8FFF0FFF36194FEF201D0F6AA" blockId="12.[151,1436,258,429]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Members of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D4BFFF0FFF36057FEF30588F61B" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[340,471,258,284]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">
<emphasis id="B97CEADAFFF0FFF36057FEF30588F61B" box="[340,471,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. robustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group are recognized by the combination of the following characteristics: 1) small to moderate size, ca. 
<quantity id="4CF09B2DFFF0FFF360CAFED60630F646" box="[457,623,294,321]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.1799999999999997" metricValueMax="4.26" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" unit="mm" value="3.1799999999999997" valueMax="4.26" valueMin="2.1">2.10–4.26 mm</quantity>
; 2) male genitalia stout, aedeagus wide in both dorsal/ventral and lateral views, with rounded apex; 3) parameres narrow, apices arcing over aedeagus; 4) pseudoparameres present, in all except 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D4BFFF0FFF361CEFE9F0519F68F" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[205,326,366,392]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffusus">
<emphasis id="B97CEADAFFF0FFF361CEFE9F0519F68F" box="[205,326,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. diffusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is tentatively placed in this group. Currently, four species are recognized: 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D4BFFF0FFF365DAFE9F0119F68F" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[1241,1350,367,392]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curvus">
<emphasis id="B97CEADAFFF0FFF365DAFE9F0119F68F" box="[1241,1350,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. curvus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D4BFFF0FFF36450FE9F048EF6AB" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2021" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diffusus">
<emphasis id="B97CEADAFFF0FFF36450FE9F048EF6AB" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. diffusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D4BFFF0FFF361DCFE6305F8F6AB" box="[223,423,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="radhakishunae">
<emphasis id="B97CEADAFFF0FFF361DCFE6305F8F6AB" box="[223,423,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">H. radhakishunae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="B97CEADAFFF0FFF360B6FE620637F6AB" box="[437,616,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C084D4BFFF0FFF360E5FE630637F6AB" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[486,616,402,428]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="robustus">H. robustus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
. All four species are only known from southern 
<collectingCountry id="F31F7658FFF0FFF36584FE620094F6AB" box="[1159,1227,402,428]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Brazil</collectingCountry>
and/or 
<collectingCountry id="F31F7658FFF0FFF36422FE6301D4F6AA" box="[1313,1419,403,429]" name="Paraguay" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
